==詞源==
多個歷史學家相信舒沙源於[[波斯語|新波斯語]]「Shīsha」（玻璃杯、水瓶）。根據《Oxford Concise Dictionary of World Place-Names》，當伊朗統治者[[阿迦·穆罕默德汗|阿迦·穆罕默德汗]]領兵到該鎮，據說他向伊布拉希姆·哈里汗說

{{Quote|
上帝正在把石頭倒在你的頭上。那時你們不要坐在你的玻璃堡壘裡。
}}

舒沙原名是「帕那哈巴德」（Panahabad），帕那之城，紀念[[卡拉巴赫汗國|卡拉巴赫汗國]]的開國君主{{en-link|帕那·阿里汗|Panah Ali Khan}}。

根據出版於[[俄羅斯帝國|俄羅斯帝國]]末年的《[[布羅克豪斯和葉夫龍百科詞典|布羅克豪斯和葉夫龍百科詞典]]》，該鎮名稱來自附近的Shushikend村（亞美尼亞語叫「Shosh」），用阿塞拜疆語<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/brokgauz_efron/117414/Шуша |title=Brockhaus and Efron Encyclopedic Dictionary |access-date=2021-09-07 |archive-date=2019-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407170744/https://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/brokgauz_efron/117414/%D0%A8%D1%83%D1%88%D0%B0 |url-status=live }}</ref>直譯就是指「舒沙村」。<ref>{{cite book |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Şuşakənd |url=http://www.lib.az/users/1/upload/files/Azrbaycan_toponimlrinin_ensiklopedik_II.pdf |location=Baku |publisher=Encyclopedia of Azerbaijani toponyms |page=304 |date=2007 |isbn=978-9952-34-156-0 |access-date=2020-12-31 |archive-date=2021-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712153142/http://www.lib.az/users/1/upload/files/Azrbaycan_toponimlrinin_ensiklopedik_II.pdf |url-status=live }}</ref>另一邊廂，亞美尼亞歷史學家利奧（1860–1932）認為它更有可能是Shosh村取名於舒沙堡，他相信舒沙是更早的定居點。<ref name="Shahen">{{cite book|last=Mkrtchyan|first=Shahen|url=https://artsakhlib.am/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Mkrtchyan-Shahen-Lernayin-Karabaghi-hushardzannery-1.pdf|title=Լեռնային Ղարաբաղի պատմա-ճարտարապետական հուշարձանները|date=1980|publisher=Hayastan publishing house|location=Yerevan|page=146|language=hy|trans-title=Historical-architectural monuments of Mountainous Karabakh|chapter=City of Shushi (Շուշի քաղաքը)|access-date=2020-12-16|archive-date=2021-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210714030926/https://artsakhlib.am/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Mkrtchyan-Shahen-Lernayin-Karabaghi-hushardzannery-1.pdf|url-status=live}}</ref>

根據亞美尼亞資料，舒沙可能源自亞美尼亞方言詞「shosh」/「shush」（亞美尼亞語：շոշ/շուշ），意思是樹發芽或引申義，高處，最早用於附近的Shosh或舒沙本身。<ref>{{Cite web|last=Danielyan|first=Samvel|date=2021-02-19|title=Շուշիի բոլոր անվանումները՝ հայերեն, թե օտարալեզու, հայկական են - Հայտարարում է բանասիրական գիտությունների թեկնածու Արտակ Վարդանյանը|trans-title=All of Shushi's names, Armenian or foreign-language, are Armenian - states Candidate of Philological Sciences Artak Vardanyan|url=https://www.aravot.am/2021/02/20/1172207/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-03-26|website=www.aravot.am|language=hy|quote=The most reliable version of the etymology of the name of the fortified city of Shushi is that it came from the Artsakh dialect's shosh (tree sprout, high place, height)... The name of the village Shosh, not far from Shushi, obviously also comes from this.|archive-date=2021-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210220092050/https://www.aravot.am/2021/02/20/1172207/}}</ref>一個民間流傳的說法是「shosh」在卡拉巴赫方言的另一個字義，引申自俄語「шоссе」，指街道或高速公路。不過這並不大可能，因為舒沙和Shosh的名稱遠早於俄語對亞美尼亞語的影響。<ref>{{cite web|last=Dalalyan|first=Tork|title=Շուշի տեղանունը, ծագումն ու ստուգաբանությունը [լեզվաբան-բանագետ Տորք Դալալյանն է պարզաբանում]|trans-title=The place name Shushi, origin and etymology (linguist-philologist Tork Dalayan explains)|url=https://www.vnews.am/culture/shushi-texanuny-tsagumn-u-stugabanutyuny/|url-status=live|access-date=2020-12-16|date=2020-11-09|publisher=vnews.am|quote=The link with շոշ (Rus. шоссе < from French) is likewise unlikely, as that word was borrowed into Armenian relatively recently, while the placenames Shushi and Shosh are older.|archive-date=2021-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210907165525/https://www.vnews.am/culture/shushi-texanuny-tsagumn-u-stugabanutyuny/}}</ref>在15世紀亞美尼亞手稿中首次書面提及舒沙時，該名稱被記錄為「Shushu」。<ref name="Shushu">Khachikyan L. S., (1955), [http://serials.flib.sci.am/openreader/nyut_hay_jogh_patm_6/book/index.html#page/452/mode/2up Memorial records in Armenian manuscripts of 15 c., Part I (1401–1450)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213231250/http://serials.flib.sci.am/openreader/nyut_hay_jogh_patm_6/book/index.html#page/452/mode/2up |date=2014-12-13 }}, Publish. of Academy of Sciences of ArmSSR, p. 384. (in [[Armenian_language|Armenian]])</ref>除了常用的亞美尼亞語名Shushi以外，歷年來該鎮在亞美尼亞語有許多不同的叫法，包括「Shoshi/Shushva Berd」、「Shoshi Sghnakh」、「Shoshvaghala」，全部指「Shosh/舒沙要塞」；當地也曾經簡單被稱為「Kala/Ghala」，即要塞。其他古代名稱包括「Shikakar Berd」（紅石堡），「Karaglkhi Sghnakh」（石上要塞），或純粹叫「Kar」（「石頭」，相對於對面的村莊Karintak（达沙尔特），「石頭下」）。<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Շուշի|encyclopedia=Հայաստանի եւ հարակից շրջանների տեղանունների բառարան [Dictionary of toponymy of Armenia and adjacent territories]|publisher=Yerevan State University Publishing House|location=Yerevan|url=http://www.nayiri.com/imagedDictionaryBrowser.jsp?dictionaryId=61&dt=HY_HY&pageNumber=3237|date=1998|volume=4|pages=161|language=hy}}</ref>

